   <group id="AmstradCpc">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Designed to be as luxurious as possible for a home computer, it was the second British home computer after ZX Spectrum. It was not plugged into a TV, instead it came with a monitor.</orig>
     <transl>它设计得尽可能豪华，作为家用电脑，是继 ZX Spectrum 之后的第二款英国家用电脑。它不是连接到电视上，而是配备了显示器。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Apple2">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Despite the advent of Macintosh (1984), modest Apple{{_}}II generated most of company’s income. It came with a monitor (probably because of short-lived regulations{{-}}consoles made lots of interference to nearby TV sets), but the monitor was connected using composite wire, like TV (composite input was rare those years).</orig>
     <transl>尽管 Macintosh（1984年）已经出现，但朴素的 Apple{{_}}II 仍是苹果公司的主要收入来源。它配备了显示器（可能是因为短暂的法规规定——控制台会对附近的电视机造成大量干扰），但显示器是通过复合线连接的，就像电视一样（那些年复合输入很少见）。</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Unenc">
     <orig>Apple logo</orig>
     <transl>苹果 Logo</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Aquarius">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>The computer was obsolete from the beginning, and was produced for a few months only.</orig>
     <transl>这台电脑从一开始就过时了，只生产了几个月。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Atari400">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>TV consoles made lots of interference to nearby TV sets, and that led to new regulations on radio frequency hardware (later they were weakened). To make a computer pluggable to TV’s aerial socket, Atari ended up with cast aluminum case and a ROM cartridge inside. The computer’s video architecture resembled a console (scrolling text and hardware sprites) and was praised for ease of programming.</orig>
     <transl>电视控制台会对附近的电视机造成大量干扰，这导致了关于射频硬件的新规定（后来这些规定被放宽了）。为了使电脑可以插入电视的天线插座，Atari 最终采用了铸铝外壳和内置的 ROM 卡。电脑的视频架构类似于控制台（滚动文本和硬件精灵），并且因其编程简便而受到称赞。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="AtariSt">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Atari did not survive the 1983 video game crisis and was sold to Jack Tramiel, the former founder of Commodore. They made the second advanced home computer after the Commodore Amiga. Musicians praised it, and music editors ''Cubase'' and ''Logic Pro'' originated from ST.</orig>
     <transl>Atari 没有挺过 1983 年的视频游戏危机，并被卖给了 Commodore 的前创始人 Jack Tramiel。他们制造了继 Commodore Amiga 之后的第二台先进的家用电脑。它受到了音乐家的称赞，音乐编辑器“Cu 基底”和“Logic Pro”就源自 ST。</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Unenc">
     <orig>Atari logo, 2×2 portrait</orig>
     <transl>Atari 标志，2×2 肖像</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="BbcMaster">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Was created by Acorn Computers as the second educational computer (after BBC Micro). It had a nice graphical OS, but it was a strange computer that aimed at several niches and hit none. Low price and TV support led to 8-bit processor and non-square pixel, and the scientific model was cancelled because of low memory.</p>
      <p />
      <p>A later model had a second Intel CPU, but IBM compatibility was basic{{-}}though it could run several important programs like ''Turbo{{_}}C'', and with memory expansion module even ''WordPerfect''.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>由 Acorn 计算机创建，作为第二款教育电脑（继 BBC Micro 之后）。它拥有不错的图形操作系统，但这款电脑针对多个细分市场却未能成功打入任何一个。低价和电视支持导致其采用了 8 位处理器和非方形像素，科学模型因内存不足而被取消。</p>
      <p />
      <p>后来的型号配备了第二个 Intel CPU，但与 IBM 的兼容性较差——尽管它可以运行一些重要的程序如 ''Turbo{{_}}C''，并且在增加内存扩展模块后甚至可以运行 ''WordPerfect''。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="C64">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Commodore 64, the main American home computer, inherited encoding from the earlier Commodore PET. It put the formula of home computers “many colours, low resolution” to the limit: the main mode for games was 160×200, 16 colours total, 4 colours per 4×8 cell. For comparison, IBM CGA had 320×200, 4 colours and no clash cells. Those 16 colours were very drab, making games more realistic.</orig>
     <transl>Commodore 64，这台主要的美国家用电脑，采用了早期 Commodore PET 的编码。它将家用电脑的“多种颜色，低分辨率”的公式发挥到了极致：游戏的主要模式是 160×200，总共 16 种颜色，每 4×8 单元格 4 种颜色。相比之下：IBM CGA 有 320×200，4 种颜色且没有冲突单元格。这 16 种颜色非常暗淡，这使得游戏更加逼真。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="CoCo">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Completely incompatible with old TRS-80, it was a low-cost home computer.</orig>
     <transl>它与旧的 TRS-80 完全不兼容，是一台低成本的家用电脑。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Hp">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>HP terminals</orig>
     <transl>HP 终端</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Rather rare and not so famous as DEC terminals.</orig>
     <transl>相当罕见，且不如 DEC 终端那么有名。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Ibm">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>PC became the ''de facto'' standard in the late 1980s: it had been cloned in 1982, and newer models became more and more powerful, retaining compatibility with old software. Games were poor initially, but VGA (320×200, 256 colours, 1987) and sheer CPU power made possible rather nice games{{-}}and, more importantly, diverse, not restricted by low memory or capabilities of the graphic accelerator.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Another IBM’s strengths were excellent text quality (80×25 cells 9×16 each in later adapters) and ease of localization (done completely in software).</p>
      <p />
      <p>For many years it ran obsolete DOS, until Microsoft presented Windows{{_}}95. Earlier OS like Unix or Windows{{_}}NT were rare.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Most modern general-purpose computers are descendants of IBM compatibles (DOS compatibility was finally broken in the 2010s). Only portable and special-purpose systems use other architectures.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>到 20 世纪 80 年代末，这台电脑已成为“事实上的”标准：它在 1982 年被克隆，新型号越来越强大，同时保持了与旧软件的兼容性。游戏最初很匮乏，但 VGA（320×200，256 色，1987 年）和纯粹的 CPU 性能使得相当不错的游戏成为可能——而且，更重要的是，游戏多样化，不再受低内存或图形加速器功能的限制。</p>
      <p />
      <p>IBM 的另一优势是出色的文本质量（在后续适配器中，每个单元格为 9×16，共 80×25 个单元格）以及易于本地化（完全通过软件进行）。</p>
      <p />
      <p>多年来，它一直运行着过时的 DOS，直到Microsoft推出了Windows{{_}}95。像 Unix  或Windows{{_}}NT 这样的早期操作系统很少见。</p>
      <p />
      <p>大多数现代通用计算机都是 IBM 兼容机的后代（DOS 兼容性最终在 2010 年代被打破）。只有便携式和专用系统使用其他架构。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
    <text id="SalesNote">
     <orig>(IBM only, ≈60M with clones by 1989)</orig>
     <transl>（仅 IBM，到 1989 年连同克隆机约 6000 万台）</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="MemNote">
     <orig>(until 1990)</orig>
     <transl>（直到 1990 年）</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Kaypro">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>The company found an interesting niche: they made very advanced 8-bit computers. In 1984 they switched to IBM compatibles, but the time had gone, and by 1990 they filed bankruptcy.</orig>
     <transl>这家公司找到了一个有趣的细分市场：他们制造了非常先进的 8 位电脑。1984 年，他们转向 IBM 兼容机，但为时已晚，到 1990 年他们破产了。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Korvet">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Korvet</orig>
     <transl>Korvet</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>The most advanced educational computer of the USSR. The computer was interesting and had good graphics, but production quality was poor, and 8-bit CPU was too weak for it, there were few scrolling games. After the fall of the USSR, cases made for Korvet were reused for smaller computers.</p>
      <p />
      <p>In one of the smoothest Korvet games, ''Rally'', only cars were graphical, the road was made with [[pt:pseudographics|pseudographics]].</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>这台电脑很有趣，图形也很好，但生产质量很差，而且 8 位 CPU 对它来说太弱了，只有少数滚动游戏。苏联解体后，为 Korvet 制作的机箱被重新用于更小的电脑。</p>
      <p />
      <p>在 Korvet 最流畅的游戏“Rally”中，只有汽车是图形的，道路是用 [[pt:pseudographics|伪图形]] 制作的。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Mac">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Mac had mouse and excellent OS, and its encoding was not encumbered with [[pt:pseudographics|pseudographics]], so it was praised by typesetters. Most design software, including ''Adobe Photoshop'', came from Mac. But the first colour Mac came only in 1987. The same Mac became 32-bit.</p>
      <p />
      <p>System fonts had UI symbols in non-standard positions, author of ''Unicodia'' attempted to find them all.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>Mac 配备了鼠标和出色的操作系统，其编码没有受到 [[pt:pseudographics|伪图形]] 的困扰，因此受到了排版人员的称赞。大多数设计软件，包括“Adobe Photoshop”，都源自 Mac。但第一台彩色 Mac 直到 1987 年才出现。同一款 Mac 也变成了 32 位。</p>
      <p />
      <p>系统字体中的 UI 符号位于非标准位置，「Unicodia」作者试图找到它们全部。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
    <text id="SalesNote">
     <orig>(until 1990)</orig>
     <transl>（直到 1990 年）</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Unenc">
     <orig>Apple logo</orig>
     <transl>苹果 Logo</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="MemNote">
     <orig>(classic Motorola 68000, until 1994)</orig>
     <transl>（经典的 Motorola 68000，直到 1994 年）</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Minitel">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Terminals were installed for free, the fee was collected for minutes of usage (equivalent of 30€¢ per minute). The system provided messaging, dating, phone directory, games, ticket booking, and more. France even had a small “dotcom bubble”, long before American in 2000! The system was closed only in 2012.</orig>
     <transl>终端是免费安装的，费用按使用分钟数收取（每分钟相当于 30 欧分）。该系统提供消息传递、约会、电话簿、游戏、票务预订等功能，以及更多。法国甚至在 2000 年美国之前就有了一个小型的“网络泡沫”！该系统直到 2012 年才关闭。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Msx">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Japanese open standard of home computers, made by Sony, Philips and others. Well-known games ''Bomberman'' and ''Metal Gear'' were initially made for these computers. USSR attempted to use them as educational computers, dubbed KUVT Yamaha.</orig>
     <transl>这是由索尼、飞利浦等公司制定的日本家用电脑的开放标准。著名的游戏“Bomberman”和“Metal Gear”最初就是为这些电脑制作的。苏联曾尝试将它们用作教育电脑，称为 KUVT Yamaha。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Ohio">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>The compaby sold early hobbyist computers, and was acquired in 1980 by telecommunication company M/A-COM that experienced financial troubles themselves.</orig>
     <transl>这家公司销售早期的业余电脑，并于 1980 年被遇到财务困难的电信公司 M/A-COM 收购。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Oric">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Not a successful computer, it was cloned in Yugoslavia (Nova 64) and Bulgaria (Pravetz 8D).</orig>
     <transl>这是一台不成功的电脑，它在南斯拉夫（Nova 64）和保加利亚（Pravetz 8D）被克隆。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="RiscOs">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Acorn Archimedes, RISC PC and others were in limited use by professionals (television, musicians) until IBM compatibles running Windows{{_}}NT and Unix drove them out.</orig>
     <transl>Acorn Archimedes、RISC PC 等电脑在专业领域（电视、音乐）中有限使用，直到运行 Windows{{_}}NT 和 Unix 的 IBM 兼容机将它们淘汰。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Robotron">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Almost never sold to customers, it was used as an educational computer.</orig>
     <transl>它几乎从未卖给过客户，而是被用作教育电脑。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Smalltalk">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Early editions of language had their own special characters.</orig>
     <transl>该语言的早期版本有它们自己的特殊字符。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Spectrum">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>ZX Spectrum was the main British home PC: it was cheap (&amp;lt;200 pounds), and had diverse games. It had no graphic acceleration, and all games except the simplest were really slow.</p>
      <p />
      <p>The most interesting story started in late 80s: DIYers from Eastern Bloc reconstructed the graphic chip out of discrete logic gates, and Spectrum clones became the main computers of the xUSSR for a brief time, until Windows and increased income made [[po:Ibm|IBM compatibles]] more widespread.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>ZX Spectrum 是英国主要的家用电脑：它很便宜（&lt;200英镑），并且游戏种类繁多。它没有图形加速，除了最简单的游戏外，所有游戏都非常慢。</p>
      <p />
      <p>最有趣的故事发生在 20 世纪 80 年代末：来自东欧的 DIY 爱好者用离散逻辑门重建了图形芯片， Spectrum 克隆机在 xUSSR 短暂地成为主要的电脑，直到 Windows 和收入增加使得 [[po:Ibm|IBM 兼容机]] 更加普及。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
    <text id="MemNote">
     <orig>(early 16K version was rare, and conversion kit to 48K existed)</orig>
     <transl>（早期的 16K 版本很少见，并且有转换为 48K 的套件）</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="SalesNote">
     <orig>(Sinclair’s original)</orig>
     <transl>（Sinclair 的原装产品）</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="SharpMz">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>It had no programming languages in ROM, and thus boasted several languages developed by competing companies. But the user had to load them from cassette or disk.</orig>
     <transl>它没有在 ROM 中预装编程语言，因此拥有多家竞争公司开发的多种语言。但用户必须从磁带或磁盘中加载它们。</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Unenc">
     <orig>Pac-Man</orig>
     <transl>Pac-Man</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Teletext">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>teletext</orig>
     <transl>图文电视</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="YearNote">
     <orig>(first TV sets)</orig>
     <transl>（首批电视机）</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Teletext transmits text and [[pt:pseudographics|pseudographics]] in blanking fields of TV signal. Nowadays most channels transmit only subtitles.</orig>
     <transl>图文电视在电视信号的消隐间隔中传输文字和 [[pt:pseudographics|伪图形]]。如今，大多数频道仅传输字幕。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Trs80">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>The computer was sold in RadioShack, Tandy’s chain of electronic stores. It had lots of innate problems, from radio interferences to poorly working cassette interface. Later models had diskettes.</orig>
     <transl>这款电脑是在 RadioShack（也就是 Tandy 旗下的电子连锁店）销售的。它天生就有很多毛病，从无线电干扰到运行不畅的磁带接口都是问题。后来的型号才改用软盘。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="Zx80">
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Sinclair ZX80 and ZX81 were the cheapest working computers. Version with 2 kilobytes was sold for 70 pounds.</orig>
     <transl>Sinclair ZX80 和 ZX81 是最便宜的可用计算机。2 千字节版本的售价为 70 英镑。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <text id="See">
    <orig>See [[pt:legacy|Legacy computers]].</orig>
    <transl>参见 [[pt:legacy|旧式计算机]]。</transl>
   </text>
  </group>
  <group id="Brk">
   <group id="BK">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/mandatory break</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 强制性中断</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>This character forcefully breaks a line. But CR+LF (0D+0A) is one break rather than two.</orig>
     <transl>这个字符会强制换行。但 CR+LF（0D+0A）被视为一次换行，而不是两次。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="CM">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/control and marks</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 控制字符与标记</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break a line before [[pt:control|control]] characters and [[pt:combining|marks]].</orig>
     <transl>不要在 [[pt:control|控制]] 字符和 [[pt:combining|标记]] 之前换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="WJ">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/word joiner</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 词连接符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break a line before and after [[pu:2060]] Word joiner.</orig>
     <transl>不要在 [[pu:2060]] 词连接符的前面或后面换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="ZW">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/zero-width space</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 零宽空格</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>You can break a line at [[pu:200B]] Zero-width space.</orig>
     <transl>你可以在 [[pu:200B]] 零宽空格处换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="GL">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/glue</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 连接符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>'''Important''' (mandatory) rule: Do not break after [[pu:00A0]] No-break space and related characters.</p>
      <p />
      <p>'''Soft''' (tailorable) rule: Do not break before these characters. However, you can break after spaces and hyphens.</p>
     </orig>
     <au-cmt>You CAN translate char name to your language</au-cmt>
     <transl>
      <p>'''重要'''（强制性）规则：不要在 [[pu:00A0]] 不换行空格及相关字符后面换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>'''软性'''（可定制）规则：不要在这些字符前面换行。不过，你可以在空格和连字符后面换行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="SP">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/space</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 空格</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>You can break after a chain of [[pu:0020]] spaces, unless other characters prohibit this.</orig>
     <au-cmt>You CAN translate char name to your language</au-cmt>
     <transl>你可以在一连串 [[pu:0020]] 空格后面换行，除非有其他字符禁止这样做。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="ZWJ">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Important/zero-width joiner</orig>
     <transl>重要 / 零宽连接符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Do not break after U+200D [[pt:zwj|Zero-width joiner]].</p>
      <p />
      <p>You can only break between [[pu:0020]] space and ZWJ.</p>
     </orig>
     <au-cmt>You CAN translate char name to your language</au-cmt>
     <transl>
      <p>不要在 U+200D [[pt:zwj|零宽连接符]] 后面换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>你只能在 [[pu:0020]] 空格和零宽连接符之间换行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="B2">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Break/before and after</orig>
     <transl>换行 / 在前面和后面</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>You can break before and after [[pu:2014]] Em dash, unless other characters prohibit.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Do not break chains of dashes, even after spaces.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>你可以在 [[pu:2014]] 长破折号的前面或后面换行，除非有其他字符禁止这样做。</p>
      <p />
      <p>不要断开一连串的破折号，即使中间有空格也不行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="BA">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Break/after</orig>
     <transl>换行 / 在后面</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>You can break after these characters.</orig>
     <transl>你可以在这些字符后面换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="BB">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Break/before</orig>
     <transl>换行 / 在前面</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>You can break before these characters. All six European characters are from dictionaries.</orig>
     <au-cmt>six as of U18</au-cmt>
     <transl>你可以在这些字符前面换行。这六个欧洲字符都来自词典。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="HY">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Break/hyphen-minus</orig>
     <transl>换行 / 连字符（减号）</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>[[pu:002D]] Hyphen-minus can have a multitude of uses: hyphen, minus, numeric dash. If further analysis shows it’s a hyphen, you can break after it by [[pl:HH|hyphen’s]] rules.</orig>
     <transl>[[pu:002D]] 连字符（减号）有多种用途：连字符、减号、数字分隔符。如果进一步分析显示它是连字符，那么你可以按照 [[pl:HH|连字符的]] 规则在它后面换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="HH">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Break/unambiguous hyphen</orig>
     <transl>换行 / 明确连字符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>You can break after a hyphen.</p>
      <p />
      <p>You cannot break before/after Hebrew text, after word-initial hyphen (-ing).</p>
      <p />
      <p>Some languages (Portuguese) use special rules for breaking hyphens:</p>
      <p>* disparate → dispara- / te</p>
      <p>* dispara-te → dispara- / -te</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>你可以在连字符后面换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>你不能在希伯来语文本的前面或后面换行，也不能在词首连字符（比如 -ing）的后面换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>有些语言（比如葡萄牙语）对连字符的断行有特殊规则：</p>
      <p>* disparate → dispara- / te</p>
      <p>* dispara-te → dispara- / -te</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="CB">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Break/conditional</orig>
     <transl>换行 / 条件</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>You can or cannot break near [[pu:FFFC]] Object replacement character depending on object type.</orig>
     <transl>你可以在 [[pu:FFFC]] 对象替换字符附近换行，也可以不换行，这取决于对象的类型。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="CL">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/closing punctuation</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 结束标点</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break before these characters, even after spaces.</orig>
     <transl>不要在这些字符前面换行，即使前面有空格也不行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="CP">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/closing parenthesis</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 闭合括号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Do not break before these characters, even after spaces.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Do not break between non-CJK closing parentheses and letters/numbers.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>不要在这些字符前面换行，即使前面有空格也不行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>不要在非中日韩（CJK）闭合括号与字母或数字之间换行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="EX">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/exclamation and interrogation</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 感叹号和问号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break before these characters, even after spaces.</orig>
     <transl>不要在这些字符前面换行，即使前面有空格也不行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="IN">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/inseparable</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 不可分割</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>These characters are often used in chains. Do not break these chains.</orig>
     <transl>这些字符经常成串使用。不要断开这些字符串。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="NS">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/non-starting</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 非起始</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>These characters cannot start a line. Do not break before them, even after spaces.</orig>
     <transl>这些字符不能作为一行的开头。不要在这些字符前面换行，即使前面有空格也不行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="OP">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/opening punctuation</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 开始标点</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Do not break after these characters, even if they are followed with spaces.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Do not break between letters/numbers and non-CJK openinng punctuation.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>不要在这些字符后面换行，即使后面有空格也不行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>不要在字母或数字与非中日韩（CJK）开启标点之间换行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="QU">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Prohibit/quote</orig>
     <transl>禁止 / 引号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Quotes can be opening or closing depending on context. They can break for themselves, without spaces, in CJK context only.</orig>
     <transl>引号根据上下文可以是开启的，也可以是闭合的。只有在中文、日文、韩文（CJK）的语境下，它们才可以在没有空格的情况下自行换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="IS">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Numeric/infix</orig>
     <transl>数字 / 中缀符号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>In numbers: it’s a part of number, do not break.</p>
      <p />
      <p>In words: do not break before these characters, even after spaces.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>在数字中：它是数字的一部分，不要断开。</p>
      <p />
      <p>在文字中：不要在这些字符前面换行，即使前面有空格也不行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="NU">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Numeric/digit</orig>
     <transl>数字 / 位数</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break numbers. Do not break letters from numbers.</orig>
     <transl>不要拆分数字。不要将字母与数字分开。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="PO">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Numeric/postfix</orig>
     <transl>数字 / 后缀符号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break between numbers and these characters.</orig>
     <transl>不要在数字和这些字符之间换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="PR">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Numeric/prefix</orig>
     <transl>数字 / 前缀符号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break between these characters and numbers.</orig>
     <transl>不要在这些字符和数字之间换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="SY">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Numeric/slash</orig>
     <transl>数字 / 斜杠</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Do not break before [[pu:002F]] Slash.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Do not break after slash in numbers, in Hebrew.</p>
      <p />
      <p>You can break after slash in other places. As a side-effect, abbreviations like “w/o” get broken, and software is allowed to break here only if other opportunities are far away.</p>
     </orig>
     <au-cmt>Of course, be as patriotic as possible. In Russian: railway. In Ukrainian: used, second-hand.</au-cmt>
     <transl>
      <p>不要在斜杠（/）前面换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>在希伯来语的数字中，不要在斜杠后面换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>在其他地方，你可以在斜杠后面换行。但这会带来一个副作用：像“w/o”（without 的缩写）这样的缩写会被断开，而且软件只有在没有其他更合适的换行机会时，才被允许在这里换行。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="AK">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Brahmic/aksara (consonant)</orig>
     <transl>婆罗米系文字 / 阿克沙拉（辅音）</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Consonants are central in Brahmic scripts.</orig>
     <transl>辅音是婆罗米系文字的核心。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="AP">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Brahmic/pre-consonant</orig>
     <transl>婆罗米系文字 / 辅音前缀符号</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break between these characters and consonants.</orig>
     <transl>不要在这些字符和辅音之间换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="AS">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Brahmic/initial consonant</orig>
     <transl>婆罗米系文字 / 词首辅音</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>This character marks the beginning of the syllable.</orig>
     <transl>这个字符标志着音节的开始。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="SA">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Brahmic/context-dependent</orig>
     <transl>婆罗米系文字 / 上下文相关形式</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Complex analysis similar to auto-hyphenation is required to decide whether you can break here.</orig>
     <transl>需要类似于自动断字的复杂分析，才能决定是否可以在这里换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="VI">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Brahmic/virama</orig>
     <transl>婆罗米系文字 / 止音符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>This [[pt:virama|virama]] '''can''' be inside a syllable. So do not break around this character.</orig>
     <transl>这个 [[pt:virama|止音符（virama）]] 可能位于音节内部。因此，不要在这个字符周围换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="VF">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Brahmic/final virama</orig>
     <transl>婆罗米系文字 / 词尾止音符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>This [[pt:virama|virama]] is always at the end of a word. Do not break '''before''' consonant with this virama. But it’s safe to break '''after''' this virama.</orig>
     <transl>这个[[pt:virama|止音符（virama）]]总是位于单词的末尾。不要在这个带有止音符的辅音前面换行。但是，在这个止音符后面换行是安全的。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="AI">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>CJK/letter or ideograph</orig>
     <transl>中日韩文字 / 字母或表意文字</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>In [[pt:cjk|CJK]] text you can break here, as it were an ideograph. Otherwise, works as a letter.</orig>
     <transl>在 [[pt:cjk|中日韩]] 文本中，你可以在此处换行，就像它是一个表意文字（汉字）一样。否则，它的行为就像一个字母。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="CJ">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>CJK/conditional Japanese starter</orig>
     <transl>中日韩文字 / 日语条件起始符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Small kana (lone consonants), plus prolonged sound [[pc:30FC]]. You can break before these characters in certain contexts only (e.g. in newspapers).</orig>
     <transl>小假名（独立辅音），加上长音符号 [[pc:30FC]]。仅在特定语境下（例如在报纸中），你才可以在这些字符前面换行。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="ID">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>CJK/ideograph</orig>
     <transl>中日韩文字 / 表意文字</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>You can break between ideographs.</p>
      <p />
      <p>You cannot break ideographs from numbers.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Some non-CJK characters also fall to this class.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>你可以在表意文字（汉字）之间换行。</p>
      <p />
      <p>你不能将表意文字与数字分开。</p>
      <p />
      <p>一些非中日韩文字的字符也属于这一类。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="H2">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Hangul/initial+medial</orig>
     <transl>谚文 / 初声+中声</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break a [[ps:Hang|Korean]] syllable.</orig>
     <transl>不要拆分 [[ps:Hang|韩语]] 音节。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="H3">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Hangul/initial+medial+final</orig>
     <transl>谚文 / 初声+中声+终声</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="JL">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Hangul/initial</orig>
     <transl>谚文 / 初声</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="JV">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Hangul/medial</orig>
     <transl>谚文 / 中声</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="JT">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Hangul/final</orig>
     <transl>谚文 / 终声</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="EB">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Emoji/base</orig>
     <transl>表情符号 / 基础</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Do not break emoji from modifiers.</orig>
     <transl>不要将表情符号与修饰符分开。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="EM">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Emoji/modifier</orig>
     <transl>表情符号 / 修饰符</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="RI">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Emoji/regional indicator</orig>
     <transl>表情符号 / 区域指示符</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>Keep regional indicators in pairs.</orig>
     <transl>保持区域指示符成对出现。</transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="AL">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Alphabetic/letter</orig>
     <transl>字母 / 文字</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Do not break words. Do not break letters from numbers.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Brahmic scripts that started to use spaces also have this class.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>不要拆分单词。不要将字母与数字分开。</p>
      <p />
      <p>那些开始使用空格的婆罗米系文字也属于这一类。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <group id="HL">
    <text id="Name">
     <orig>Alphabetic/Hebrew</orig>
     <transl>字母 / 希伯来文字</transl>
    </text>
    <text id="Text">
     <orig>
      <p>Do not break words. Do not break letters from numbers.</p>
      <p />
      <p>Do not break Hebrew+hyphen+non-Hebrew.</p>
      <p />
      <p>So not break slash+Hebrew.</p>
     </orig>
     <transl>
      <p>不要拆分单词。不要将字母与数字分开。</p>
      <p />
      <p>不要将“希伯来文字+连字符+非希伯来文字”的组合拆开。</p>
      <p />
      <p>不要将“斜杠+希伯来文字”的组合拆开。</p>
     </transl>
    </text>
   </group>
   <text id="Hard">
    <orig>This rule is '''important''': must exist in some form in every program.</orig>
    <transl>这条规则非常 '''重要'''：必须以某种形式存在于每一个程序中。</transl>
   </text>
   <text id="Soft">
    <orig>This rule is '''soft''': may be removed or changed depending on language, context (mathematics, Web links etc), or program’s audience.</orig>
    <transl>这条规则是 '''软性''' 的：可以根据语言、上下文（如数学公式、网页链接等）或程序的目标受众进行移除或修改。</transl>
   </text>
   <text id="Brah">
    <orig>In some [[pt:brahmic|Brahmic]] scripts, the text may run like a solid wall without spaces, and you need to find a place for a line break{{-}}either by syllables or by words. You cannot break a syllable.</orig>
    <transl>在某些婆罗米系文字中，文本可能像一堵密不透风的墙，字与字之间没有空格。这时你需要找到合适的位置进行换行——要么按音节，要么按词。但绝对不能把一个音节拆开。</transl>
   </text>
   <text id="See">
    <orig>See [[pt:linebreak|Line breaking]].</orig>
    <transl>参见 [[pt:linebreak|换行]]。</transl>
   </text>
   <text id="Scr">
    <orig>Scripts</orig>
    <au-cmt>Scripts: Alpha, Bravo…</au-cmt>
    <transl>文字</transl>
   </text>
  </group>
 </file>
</ut>
